textBeforeTable: Season results Coachs take: We stress so much team defense and helping each other out. Its a combination of all five kids on the floor. ... Its a different person every game. I think individually those kids can do a great job, but in order for the team to deal well, it has to be team defense. Notes: The Lady Popes have doubled opponents in points scored (1,557-775) this season and are holding opposition under an average of 30 points per game. ... Pius won the 2010 state title and fell in the semifinals in both 2001 and 2011. ... Pius has had a different leading scorer almost every game this season, but junior Gabby Green is the Lady Popes only player who has averaged in double-digits with 10.9 points per game. Her 94 assists and 61 steals also lead the team. ... Pius only two losses this season have come to D1 qualifiers Kimberly and Oak Creek, who will meet in the D1 semifinals Friday. ... Senior Vivevca Nwagbaraocha leads the team in rebounding (4.5 rebounds per game), but the team has only 10 blocks all season. ... Neither Notre Dame nor Pius has a player on its roster taller than 5-foot-11. Last time at state: 2011. State appearances: Four. Season record: 24-2 (17-0, Woodland West Conference, first place). Miles from Resch Center: 120. Enrollment: 873. Coach: Scott Herrick (222-52,
